    "description": "Margo is back! <br>Armed with a strong hunger for vindication as well as a dubious psychotherapeutical coping mechanism, she sets out to tie up the loose ends she left behind. <br><br>While getting used to her new life as a capable, collected young woman, an unexpected letter draws her into a mysterious plot. Facing many new demanding challenges, will she stay on top of things?<br><br>Equip Margo with all the best gear (the Scarf of Social Bravery, anyone?), find just the right artifacts, solve the occasional puzzle and settle the score with her old nemeses. <br><br>Midnight Margo is a narrative-driven roleplaying adventure with a touch of absurdity. It deals with topics such as existential anxiety and social conflict, but also offers occasionally dark humour as well as puzzle-solving.<br><br>Midnight Margo features <br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> A superb cast of voice actors that bring the dialogues to life<br></li><li> Unique photo collage graphics, mixed with handpainted elements <br></li><li> An atmospheric soundtrack by composer Jacob Lincke<br></li><li> Moral dilemmas <br></li><li> A plethora of colourful characters<br>and more.</li></ul><br>Expected release: First half of 2024<br>Wishlist now!",
